        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The scheme &amp;quot;Schemes for Welfare of School Children Belonging to BPL and BC(A) families: Monthly Stipend for BPL Students&amp;quot; was launched by the Government of Haryana during the financial year 2009-10. It aims to provide financial assistance to students from Below Poverty Line (BPL) families to support their education. Under this scheme, a monthly stipend is provided to students from BPL families studying in classes 1 to 12 in Haryana Government schools.\n",
        "benefits_md": "**A.  For Girl Students:**\n\n   1. Class 1 to 5: ₹150/- per month\n   1. Class 6 to 8: ₹200/- per month\n   1. Class 9 to 12: ₹300/- per month\n   1. Class 11 to 12 **(Science Students only)**: ₹400/- per month\n**A.  For Boy Students:**\n\n   1. Class 1 to 5: ₹75/- per month\n   1. Class 6 to 8: ₹100/- per month\n   1. Class 9 to 12: ₹150/- per month\n   1. Class 11 to 12 **(Science Students only)**: ₹200/- per month\n> **Mode of Disbursement:**\n\n> Direct transfer to students&#39; bank accounts.\n\n> **Frequency of Disbursement:**\n\n> Monthly basis.\n\n> **Expected Time of Disbursement:**\n\n> Funds to be transferred at the beginning of each quarter.\n\n> **Validity:**\n\n> Applicable for the duration of the academic session.\n\n> Attendance criteria: Minimum 50% attendance required for next installment\n\n",
        "exclusions_md": "\n1. The applicant who does not maintain 50% attendance will not receive the next instalment.\n1. The applicant not studying in a Haryana Government school is ineligible.\n\n",
        "briefDescription": "The scheme aims to provide financial assistance to students from BPL students to support their education. Under this scheme, a monthly stipend is provided to students studying in classes 1 to 12 in Haryana Government schools.",
        "detailedDescription": [
